{
  "stem": "20089.3",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 13.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And so it was difficult for me to realize that there were black marketeers in the world, and there were people who wanted Palestine to be Israel, and that I wasn't cooperating with them the way I should have.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I think also the-- the relations, my-- my uncle and his black marketeer-- black market activities were not something that I accepted very lightly-- again, through immaturity, not through any idealism.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I think the most rewarding experience for me was the fact that I was able to establish nursery schools, that I was able to give the children an education, the fact that the people at the camp felt that I was helping them, and the fact that when they left, they left in gratitude, not in anger.",
      "word_count": 57
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In February '47.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, yes.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I went to work in the Municipal Social-- Department of Municipal Social Work.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And then when I got married, I gave up social work and worked in nursery schools.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The Southern-- Southern [INAUDIBLE] Nursery School, and then Oxford Nursery School.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In Johannesburg, yes.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Strangely enough, no.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The impact came very much later.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "My immediate return-- was to get married, and to have a family, and to talk about my work in Germany, because there were very few people who knew about it.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I gave quite a lot of public talks about work in the displaced persons camps, but not with the kind of impact that it had when I was much older, when I actually wrote the manuscript that I did.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Then I relived it much more so than I did at first.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I was too busy working at nursery schools and bringing up a family to really be bothered about what-- what I had gone through.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Well, I hadn't gone through anything.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
